{
  "text": "Ileus is an an important group of conditions causing acute abdominal pain. Typical clinical signs of ileus are abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, and blockage of the passage of stool and gas [CITATION_1] . Napkin has never been known as a cause of alimentary tract obstruction. In the present case, the patient suffered from gastrointestinal obstruction due to a napkin in the ileum.",
